						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar in the Brahmalingēśvara temple in the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Ānanda, Phālguṇa śu. 11, Monday.</p>						

						<p>Records the gift of 10 puṭṭis of land to the Chennēśvara temple, the cultivation of which seems to have been entrusted to the stone-masons of Koṇḍapura by Saraya-mahāpātra. In characters of the 15th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
